    "body": "### Prerequisites\r\n\r\n* [ ] Put an X between the brackets on this line if you have done all of the following:\r\n    * Reproduced the problem in Safe Mode: http://flight-manual.atom.io/hacking-atom/sections/debugging/#using-safe-mode\r\n    * Followed all applicable steps in the debugging guide: http://flight-manual.atom.io/hacking-atom/sections/debugging/\r\n    * Checked the FAQs on the message board for common solutions: https://discuss.atom.io/c/faq\r\n    * Checked that your issue isn't already filed: https://github.com/issues?utf8=âœ“&q=is%3Aissue+user%3Aatom\r\n    * Checked that there is not already an Atom package that provides the described functionality: https://atom.io/packages\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nSometimes when updating packages, Atom loses most of its settings. E.g. right now, I updated Hyperclick, and after the restart I was greeted with the welcome message, my font was reset to the default settings, my settings for linter-pycodestyle and linter-pylint were lost, and I assume all the others as well, but I didn't bother with the rest much, so no impact there in my case.\r\n\r\nThis is difficult to reproduce; I can update packages dozens of times, but every once in a while, it loses all my settings. It's not a disk full issue, as I have 56GB available.\r\n\r\nThe data loss appears to be limited to the things in ~/.atom/config.cson - the other .cson files and styles.less appear to be unaffected.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Update packages\r\n2. Restart\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** Atom restarts with upgraded packages, and settings intact.\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** Atom restarts with upgraded packages, and lost settings.\r\n\r\n**Reproduces how often:** Less than 10%\r\n\r\n### Versions\r\nAtom    : 1.18.0\r\nElectron: 1.3.15\r\nChrome  : 52.0.2743.82\r\nNode    : 6.5.0\r\napm  1.18.1\r\nnpm  3.10.10\r\nnode 6.9.5 x64\r\npython 2.7.6\r\ngit 1.9.1\r\n\r\nOS: Linux Mint 17.3 Rosa\r\nKernel: 3.19.0-32-generic #37~14.04.1-Ubuntu SMP Thu Oct 22 09:41:40 UTC 2015 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\nAny additional information, configuration or data that might be necessary to reproduce the issue.\r\n"
